        <h2>Arizona's Directly Impacted Voice for Reform</h2>
        <p>We are Praxis Initiative, Arizona's only 100% directly impacted criminal justice reform organization. Born from lived experience of incarceration, probation, and court involvement, our organization began in August 2020 as Arizonans for Transparency and Accountability in Corrections (ATAC). Every staff member, board director, and core volunteer has directly navigated Arizona's criminal legal system, giving us unmatched understanding of what reform actually requires.</p>
        <p>For four years, ATAC led the statewide campaign to create independent oversight of the Arizona Department of Corrections, Rehabilitation & Reentry (ADCRR). In 2025, that vision became reality when the Arizona Legislature passed Senate Bill 1507, establishing the Office of Independent Correctional Ombudsman. This historic victory proved that directly impacted leadership can move mountains—literally reshaping state government to be more accountable to its people. The bill passed with bipartisan support from Sen. Shawnna Bolick (R) and Sen. Analise Ortiz (D).</p>
        <p>With that milestone achieved, we expanded our mission. In 2024, ATAC evolved into Praxis Initiative, broadening our work beyond prison walls to address every stage of the criminal legal system while maintaining our fierce commitment to oversight. Our team now operates five distinct programs, all led by people who've lived the problems we're solving.</p>
