        <h2>Five Programs, One Mission</h2>
        <p>Praxis Initiative runs five interconnected programs that attack injustice at its roots. Our <strong>Independent Prison Oversight</strong> program monitors the new state oversight office while training formerly incarcerated auditors to conduct independent facility inspections. <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> targets sentencing laws, probation terms, and collateral consequences through direct legislative advocacy. <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> confronts Arizona's overdose crisis by pushing for harm reduction, treatment access, and ending prosecution-driven responses to substance use.</p>
        <p>Through <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training for Returning Citizens</strong>, we equip directly impacted individuals with tools to testify at the legislature, serve on state commissions, and lead community organizing. Our <strong>ARTS in Prison & Think Motion</strong> sends teaching artists into ADCRR facilities to facilitate music, visual arts, dance, and movement workshops that affirm humanity behind bars and build skills for post-release advocacy. Together, these programs create a pipeline from personal transformation to systemic change.</p>
